                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/New_York"
                    },
                    "body": "What would be nice is basically: one section per package manager, an up-front warning that package managers cannot be mixed, and each section can explain its own limitations (like the GCS/Homebrew issue). I don't think we want to or can be a tutorial for every single system out there, but basic instructions would be useful, and currently that page doesn't really talk about package managers at all.",
